  <description type="morphology">Stems abundantly branched, arching distally. Leaves tapering to weakly defined petioles; blades 3–10(–15) × 0.5–1.5 cm. Heads (3–)8–16 in each array, arrays usually clustered. Phyllaries 4–6(–8) mm, tips green, obtuse. Ray corollas 8–12+ mm. Disc corollas (5–)7–8+ mm. Cypselae (1.5–)2–3 mm; pappi 5–6+ mm. 2n = 60.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering year-round, mostly spring.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Open, rocky, disturbed sites;</description>
  <description type="elevation">700–1500 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Ariz., N.Mex., Tex.; Mexico; Central America.</description>
